      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OLLIE'S SECRET (2) wasn't quite at his best last start at Tamworth when tackling quality opposition but did warm nicely late to finish fifth. That followed a tough front-running win at Muswellbrook at the previous outing. Finds a suitable assignment and draws to get all the favours. Can get the job done. Nine-year-old TOULON FACTOR (5) is an absolute rock for the Clement stable and rarely puts a bad foot forward. Expect him to push forward again and give plenty of cheek. HOW'S IT KEV (1) doesn't win out of turn but boasts strong peaks. Bullock's booking signals stable confidence, so willing to forgive last two. FEIRME PRINCE (4) has been about the mark without winning, the latest effort a third over 1100m at Bathurst. Gallagher will have to be on the ball from the inside draw or he could land in a very tricky spot. RED BERYL (3) failed at the latest when in Open company but was a good win the start prior at Warren when working home strongly over the top. Will pay to keep on side.",
